  3   GROUP BY department_id
  4   HAVING AVG(salary)>10000
  5*  ORDER BY AVG(salary)
SQL> /

Wrote file afiedt.buf

  1  (SELECT e.first_name,e.last_name,e.department_id, d.department_name
  2  FROM employees e, departments d
  3  WHERE e.department_id(+)=d.department_id)
  4                               MINUS
  5  (SELECT e.first_name,e.last_name,e.department_id, d.department_name
  6  FROM employees e, departments d
  7* WHERE e.department_id=d.department_id)

Wrote file afiedt.buf

  1  select e.first_name, e.last_name, e.salary, d.department_name, l.city, c.country_name,
  2  j.job_title
  3  from employees e, departments d, locations l, countries c, jobs j
  4  where
  5  e.department_id = d.department_id
  6  and
  7  l.location_id = d.department_id
  8  and
  9  c.country_id = l.country_id
 10  and
 11* j.job_id = e.job_id
SQL> /

Wrote file afiedt.buf

  1  select e.first_name, e.Last_name, e.salary, d.department_name, d.department_id,
  2  L.city, c.country_name, j.job_title
  3  from employees e, jobs j, job_history jh, departments d, locations L, countries c
  4  where e.department_id = d.department_id
  5  and d.location_id = l.location_id
  6  and l.country_id = c.country_id
  7  and c.region_id  = r.region_id
  8  and d.department_id = jh.department_id
  9* and jh.job_id = j.job_id
SQL> /

  1  select e.first_name, e.Last_name, e.salary, d.department_name, d.department_id,
  2  L.city, c.country_name, j.job_title
  3  from employees e, jobs j, job_history jh, departments d, locations L, countries c
  4  where e.department_id = d.department_id
  5  and d.location_id = l.location_id
  6  and l.country_id = c.country_id
  7  and d.department_id = jh.department_id
  8* and jh.job_id = j.job_id

  2  L.city, c.country_name, j.job_title

  5  and e.department_id = d.department_id
  6  and d.location_id = l.location_id

  8  /

  1  CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION INCOME_TAX (salary IN NUMBER)
  2  RETURN NUMBER IS
  3  BEGIN
  4  RETURN (salary * .08625);
  5* END INCOME_TAX;
SQL> /

SQL> ed
Wrote file afiedt.buf

  1  CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE raise_salary
  2  (id NUMBER)
  3   IS
  4   BEGIN
  5   UPDATE employees
  6   SET salary=salary+(salary*10/100)
  7   WHERE employee_id =id;
  8*  END raise_salary;
  9  /
